Following the conclusion of the English Premier League, EPL, Match Day 12 fixtures on Sunday, below are the highest goal scorers chasing the golden boot in the English top-flight league. Leicester City striker, Jamie Vardy is presently the highest goal scorer in the Premier League after he scored a goal in his side’s 2-0 victory over Arsenal on Saturday to take his tally to 11 goals. Chelsea’s Tammy Abraham is second place after he scored a goal in his side’s 2-0 win over Crystal Palace on Saturday to take his tally to 10 goals. Manchester City striker, Sergio Aguero failed to score in his side’s 3-1 defeat to Liverpool on Sunday. The Argentine international has 9 goals. Premier League top scorers: 11 goals: Jamie Vardy (Leicester City) 10 goals: Tammy Abraham (Chelsea) 9 goals: Sergio Aguero (Manchester City) 8 goals: Pierre-Emerick Aubameyang (Arsenal) 7 goals: Raheem Sterling (Manchester City), Sadio Mane (Liverpool) 6 goals: Teemu Pukki (Norwich), Harry Kane (Tottenham), Mohamed Salah (Liverpool), Marcus Rashford (Manchester United). 5 goals: Callum Wilson (Bournemouth), Christian Pulisic (Chelsea), Raul Jimenez (Wolves), Danny Ings (Southampton), Chris Wood (Burnley), Ashley Barnes (Burnley), Bernardo Silva (Manchester City). 4 goals: James Maddison (Leicester), Jordan Ayew (Crystal Palace), Mason Mount (Chelsea). Download Daily Post App.    Subscribe to Daily Post Newsletter.    Advertise with us.   Send us enquiries, press releases.